name: David K Frampton 'Pop Ice' LP (Ltd cdr incl.)
description:
DKF's debut vinyl release...a heartbreaking collection of skewed electronic pop that shuffles post-dancefloor riddims underpinning DKF fraught and fragile vocals. This was produced in 24 hours and was an extremely intensive and productive night of music making presented here as 8 tracks of deep, evocative, midnight electro-soul.

If you buy through BIG CARTEL you receive free exclusive CDR entitled 'Pop Land' which presents 9 more variations on DKF' s personal apocalypse featuring cold industrial soundscapes, spoken word, grunt techno and squonky electronics...

name: Gary Goodmann + Nick Hudson/Truck Pitch/ CINIK 3 pack
description: Gary Goodman and Nick Hudson's 'January' in a triple pack with Truck Pitch 'Supplejack' and CINIK 'Light'.

name: Truck Pitch 'Supplejack' (ess030)
description:
Originally one of now legendary Process Records flagship bands, Truck Pitch emerged from the tail end of the 90's with cassette releases, EPs and one LP of constantly shifting sonics down dark corridors of sound underwhich the heartbreak of existance lurked. The music had references to danceflloor reverberations and mingled with dub, electro, noise, techno, industrial except these forms were coated in gloopy guitars, keyboards and washed out para-normal sonic lubrications.

This album sees the original duo re-united for a 2012 celebration of visceral club-through-proxy droning. Their most synth like for years, where the noise quota is set back and at the forefront are copious rolling beat-constructions.

name: CINIK 'Light' (Eyeless029)
description:
New Mexico's CINIK brings us 'Light', a concept mini album that uses different experiences of light to enter an other-worldly sonic domain that can seem unsettling, mesmeric and frighteningly intense.

'Light is a 4 track mini album that offers the listener a sonic exploration of visual stimuli. Each track represents a mood brought about by certain light environments. Fluorescence is a short piece of guitar feedback that mimics the pulsating hum of artificial lighting. Some days will be dark is a distorted and processed harmonica piece that mirrors the extended darkness of northern days without light. The last two tracks create an experience similar to watching the sun rise through the use of bowed electric bass. Drone may bore some or fill others with dread, but the sounds are something of joy and acceptance for those willing to immerse themselves in the sounds of light.' -CINIK

name: David K Frampton 'Faith Hotel 2002-2012' (ess028)
description:
A best of collection from Eyeless boss David K Frampton spanning ten years from various albums which are hard to find and no longer available.
Styles range from dream-sludge to blisteringly heavy dancefloor to outsider poems to spacepop disco. Everything is contorted into DKF's unique and effective voice displaying a knack for soaking up and distorting various sonic realities.

Each cassette is hand illustrated by David K Frampton.

Tracks:
a

1) Heaven Awaits
2) River Bed
3) Damage Control
4) Father
5) Warrior Pot
6) Fleet Of Wings
7) Rejuice!

b

8) Hidden Floors
9) Cyvarb
10) Sledgehammer
11) Chasing Tail
12) We're Gonna Rock N' Roll All Night
13) Rising Power
14) The Key

name: David K Frampton 'Ep One + Two
description:
CDR in slipcase of the first two EPs in DKFs ongoing project for 2012- an EP a month. This is special as it features the 2nd EP which will not be released digitally for 2 weeks. Dave's music includes dream-wave, outsider pop, bass teknology, spoken word and experimental sound.
Potent to the core.

name: All 3 Peace For Old Ghosts cds
description:
You can buy here the debut album by Peace For Old Ghosts 'Dawn Chorus' plus his previous two EPS 2010's 'Between' and 2008's 'The Likewise EP' for a bargain 7 pounds! 

Peace For Old Ghosts music crosses boundaries between Kraut-folk, spectral sound and singer-songwriter expression. The music is always personal but big. Desert highway big, an urban fantasy of America, a place where hearts are broken and minds are opened, a journey from his pysche to ours. And what a privelage it is to share it.

For fans of Neil Young, Wilco, Spiritualized and Terrors.

name: Pigggasm/ Partikle Accelerator/ Deaf Realist (Ess024)
description:
Extreme harsh noise on this 3 way album featuring noise from in order: Robert Ridley-Shackleton, DKF and Lee Riley.

'By the end, darkness wins out, and an ominous near-silence pads out the final minute or so. Turn the volume right up, though, and you’ll realise you’re still engulfed in the sound.'

Simon Minter
Music In Oxford

name: Peace For Old Ghosts 'Between' (ess023)
description:
Peace For Old Ghosts (Simon Shippey (Custom Blue, Ed Vallance)) new album 'Between' is a huge leap forward from 2008's The Likewise ep. This time Simon takes an instrumental approach which combines electro-acoustic, kraut-folk and country elements with a sense of deep melancholy but also of hope. Based in Brooklyn, Simon Shippey has honed his song-writing skills to perfection blending complex arrangements with rich harmonic patterns. Assisted by Jory Cunningham and Ted Meyer, 'Between' is an album not to miss. Available now for the 1st time on very ltd CDR in a plastic half-case with card inslip.

For fans of Wilco, Six Organs Of Admittance, Spiritualized, Ry Cooder.

name: Vileswarm 'The Shaman's Last Waltz' (ess022)
description:
Fizzing drone, improv free music with pysch-doom elements. The meeting of David K Frampton and Lee RIley (Euhedral/ This Is My Anarchy).

"An experimental dreamteam of Frampton and Euhedral, offering “doom drone”: does exactly what it says on the tombstone." David Murphy, Oxford Bands

"The accelerating entropy of a sick and diseased universe drenched in feedback and unsettling atmospheres" Brendan Meachen, Pixadelica

For lovers of Sunn 0)), Mouthus, The Dead C

name: Foetus 502 'Septology' (ess20)
description: Heroically epic X3 disc 7 part album by Foetus 502 who became Robert Ridley-Shackleton. Follow his journey through bastard pop, tape loop funk noise and some rare live recordings. If you are tweakin' out over his new tapes check this early incarnation!

name: Finger Pistols 'Bloomsbury EP' (ess019)
description:
See the epic London electro-rockers soar with their heavy weight big hearted lushly created pop hooks and crunchy riffs!

Check in if you're into QOTSA, Depeche Mode or Interpol

This is a unique gem in the Eyeless Experience...

name: Eyeless 001-008
description:
Any of the 1st 8 Eyeless albums by David K Frampton.
Albums were in order: 'A Snapshot Of Dying Slowly', 'Rock', 'Ten Corners', 'Prayer 36', 'A Gravitation Towards the Head', 'The Orange Room', 'Red Out' and 'Reverse'.

One pound each.
Pure outsider pop to noise to electronix.
